info.description:
wayback is a package for querying the Wayback Machine using the  Wayback
Machine API.

See:

* https://archive.org/help/wayback_api.php

for more information about the API.

Installation
============

If you have already downloaded wayback, run the following
command inside this directory::

    $ python setup.py install

If you have not yet downloaded wayback, it would be easier to use
pip::

    $ pip install wayback

or easy_install::

    $ easy_install wayback

Either method will install wayback into your current environment.

Changelog
=========

For a full history of changes see the commit history:

* https://bitbucket.org/jgoettsch/py-wayback/commits/all

Development
===========

Development for wayback takes place on bitbucket:

* https://bitbucket.org/jgoettsch/py-wayback/

To get started you can do the following::

    $ hg clone https://bitbucket.org/jgoettsch/py-wayback/
    $ cd py-wayback
    $ pip install -r requirements_dev.txt
    $ python setup.py develop

If you discover a bug, please create an issue ticket:

* https://bitbucket.org/jgoettsch/py-wayback/issues/new
